Currently this PR is providing a dummy images where the ImageField is just an empty string - I'd expect these to return nothing or render the empty block.

I think we only want dummy images as a fallback for images which are missing but should exist - which is what `get_thumbnail` does.

Let's say they have:

```
server {
  server_name example.org;
  listen 80 default_server;
}
```
Right now we would do:
```
server {
  server_name example.org;
  listen 80 default_server;
  listen 443 ssl; # note no default_server is added here, so it's 
                  # not explicitly made the default server for 443
  # rest of the ssl directives
  if (scheme) {
    redirect http->https;
  }
}
```
Instead, we will be doing:
```
server {
  server_name example.org;
  listen 80 default_server;
  redirect http->https;
}
server {
  server_name example.org;
  listen 443 ssl; # we're just as implicitly the default_server as we were before.
  # rest of the ssl directives
}
```
This is the same exact behavior as we had before.

we often try to avoid loops like this in tests in favor of either:

- parametrized fixtures
- parametrized tests

```python
@pytest.fixture(params=[1, 2, 3])
def fixture_with_params(request):
    return request.param

@pytest.mark.parmetrize('value', [1, 2, 3])
def test_that_is_parametrized(value):
    ...
```
